TITLE: A Lightning-Fast Three-Flavor Neutrino Oscillation Calculator in Constant-Density Matter with Built-In Uncertainty Propagation\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs20 \cf2 AUTHORS: Aaryan Chaulagain and Anju Dhakal
\f0\fs22 \
\
----------- Overall evaluation -----------\
SCORE: 2 (accept)\
----- TEXT:\
1- the researchers have successfully developed a fast and accurate three-flavor neutrino oscillation calculator optimized for constant-density matter. The framework effectively combines compact analytic formulations with exact diagonalization benchmarks, achieving a tenfold improvement in computational speed while maintaining percent-level accuracy across the relevant energy ranges.\
2- From a methodological perspective, the key achievement lies in the balance between speed and precision. Such a balance is often difficult to obtain, as faster computation can come at the expense of accuracy. The demonstrated ability of this tool to retain both qualities makes it suitable for both educational and research applications.\
3- Another notable contribution is the incorporation of built-in uncertainty propagation mechanisms, implemented through both Monte Carlo sampling and a Jacobian-based approach. This integration allows for the rapid construction of confidence bands without the need for computationally expensive global fits, providing researchers with an efficient means of conducting statistically robust analyses.\
4- Validation through unitarity checks, examination of resonance behavior, and performance benchmarking confirms the reliability and numerical stability of the method within its intended scope. Consequently, the tool can be viewed as a dependable resource for early-stage experimental design in neutrino physics.\
\
